body.p: Currently, in the desktop we don't have a way of changing the working directory of excution contexts. The following two cells print out the current working directory and the available environment variables.
The users home directory is at

To require a package in the you may need to specify the complete path. In Here we require d3 so we can use it's csv parsing function to read in some data (from https://github.com/datasciencedojo/datasets/, file titanic.csv).

body.p: The d3.csvParse function returns an array of objects. The table function in Mini will transform an array of objects into a data table (you maybe could do that in Node yourself):
We can then query the data table in SQLite (which is embedded in the Node.js execution context, which is embedded in the desktop)

alternatives.code: SELECT PClass, avg(Survived), avg(Fare) FROM data_table GROUP BY PClass

body.p: The error "cannot modify data_table because it's a view" is a bug and requires you to rename the data table or restart the desktop.
